OL,4,Cdriving after newborn baby died
OL,6,FOfficers said she was left with
OL,7,Fserious injuries and is still
OL,8,Frecovering after treatment in hospital.
OL,10,FThe woman was pregnant at the time of
OL,11,Fthe collision and while she underwent
OL,12,Femergency surgery to have her baby boy
OL,13,Fdelivered, he tragically later died in
OL,14,Fhospital.
OL,16,FPolice have now charged Ashir Shahid,
OL,17,F20, from Walton le Dale, with causing
OL,18,Fdeath by dangerous driving and causing
OL,19,Fserious injury by dangerous driving.
